SIMPLE: pretender
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pretender
<hw>Pre*tend"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who lays claim, or asserts a title (to something); a claimant.</def>
Specifically, <def><xex>The pretender</xex> <fld>(Eng. Hist.)</fld>, the
son or the grandson of James II., the heir of the royal family of
Stuart, who laid claim to the throne of Great Britain, from which the
house was excluded by law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is the shallow, unimproved intellects that are the confident
<qex>pretenders</qex> to certainty.</q>
<rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who pretends, simulates, or feigns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pretendership</ent>⟦br⟧
